f=Cybersecurity/bastion/operational/commands/bastion-commands.md · h1:bastion — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:bastion — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:bastion — Command Triggers=\| "cloud posture," "cloud security," "CSPM," "misconfig," "public bucket," "open port" \| cloud-posture \| /bastion-posture \| · h1:bastion — Command Triggers=\| "harden," "CIS baseline," "config baseline," "is this box secure" \| hardening-baselines \| /bastion-harden \| · h1:bastion — Command Triggers=\| "vuln," "CVE," "patch," "vulnerability scan," "are we vulnerable" \| infra-vuln-management \| /bastion-vuln \| · h1:bastion — Command Triggers=\| "network security," "segment," "firewall rule," "ZTNA," "network review" \| network-security \| /bastion-network \| · h2:Precedence=**Every gap/finding lands warden's risk-register** bastion finding resolved isolation; register tracks it. **Any privileged execution** (cloud config change, firewall rule apply, patch) operator ops deploy gate. bastion holds keys (the security-inversion). **Joint findings ops/aegis** bastion tracks infra half; ops/aegis tracks their half. finding resolved until halves confirmed. **Drift findings** (remediated gap reappeared) process gap warden, re-remediation.